title: Was the length of the coral reefs larger than the Empire State Building discovered in the Great Barrier Reef?
subtitle: It was the first separate coral reefs to be discovered in the region since the late 18th century.
author: Madison Dapcevich
vclaim: Australian scientists discovered 1,600-foot separate coral reefs in the Great Barrier Reef, making them the first to be discovered in the region over a century.
